Twin Spin

Features

How to Play

Why Play

Featuring no less than 243 paylines and five reels, NetEnt’s Twin Spin takes inspiration from the vintage slot machines of old, containing symbols such as lucky 7s, BARs, diamonds and fruit. Twin Spin is a basic video slot that is perfect to try if you’re just starting out – it does not feature the elaborate features that some of our more advanced video slots have.

Any bet your place on Twin Spin is affected by two factors, namely the bet level, and the value. You can place a bet that’s worth as little as 1 cent, or as much as €5, and the bet level acts as a bet multiplier, increasing the value of the initial bet that you placed.
Another feature of Twin Spin is that the number of paylines are set automatically, so you don’t have to worry about doing so yourself. Seeing as the video slot has 243, this feature represents a lot of different ways you can win. One thing that should be noted, however, is that winnings are paid out in proportion to the amount that you wager on the winning bet.

Twin Spin is not like other slots; for one there is always a set of twin reels which are linked together, but on top of that there's also the brilliant possibility that they will grow into triplet, quadruplets or even quintuplet reels. Twin Spin also has a Wild substitution function for added chances to win. This unique wheel has over 243 ways to win and a top prize of 270,000 coins! With a high chance of success, and a massive jackpot it's hard to resist Twin Spin. More than this though Twin Spin is a genuinely fun and exciting game with enough levels to keep players occupied spin after spin.

Responsible Gaming

Gaming can be both entertaining and profitable. But you can't always win. Losing is a part of the game and you have to be prepared for it. Read more about responsible gaming and our player protection tools here.

If you are a resident of Sweden and experiencing any potential gambling issues, you can always reach out to Stodlinjen for consultation, and independent and a third party helpline:

Support Line (Sweden)

Website: www.stodlinjen.se

Telephone: 020-81 91 00 weekdays 09:00-21:00 for players and relatives. You can also access the support line through chat, SMS or email via the web page above.

You can also access the national self-exclusion tool Spelpaus supported by the Swedish Gambling Authority. This tool is an easy way to self-exclude yourself from all licensed gambling websites in Sweden.

If you are a resident of Great Britain and are experiencing any potential gambling issues, you can always reach out to BeGambleAware for consultation, an independent and third party helpline:

Support Line (UK)

Website: begambleaware.org

Freephone: (+44) 0808 8020 133 from 8am – midnight 7 days a week

You can also access the national online self-exclusion scheme, GAMSTOP. You can use this tool to self-exclude from all BML Group Ltd websites. GAMSTOP also includes a large number of online gambling websites, but not all. In due course, all websites will be required to join.
